Summary
Completed Recipe Duplicate and Recipe Delete functionality.
Recipe records now support soft delete using a dedicated deleted flag, preserving downstream integrity and allowing future restoration.
________________________________________
Completed
Recipe Duplicate
Implemented duplicate recipe functionality from both Recipe page and Recipe List.
Behavior:
•	Creates exact copy of recipe header
•	Copies diet tags
•	Copies recipe components
•	Copies notes
•	Copies yield information
•	Copies active status
•	Opens duplicated recipe for editing
Duplicate naming:
•	Recipe Name (Copy)
•	Recipe Name (Copy 2)
•	Recipe Name (Copy 3)
•	etc.
Duplicate name generation uses existing normalization rules and respects case/accent-insensitive uniqueness.
Examples considered equivalent:
•	Tokay
•	tokay
•	Tókay
•	toKày
________________________________________
Recipe Delete
Implemented soft delete architecture.
Delete action now:
•	Sets active = false
•	Sets deleted = true
Recipe is removed from:
•	Recipe List
•	Recipe picklists
•	Component recipe selectors
Recipe remains stored in database.
Benefits:
•	Supports future restore capability
•	Preserves downstream references
•	Avoids accidental permanent data loss
